appTitle: Sniper 3D Gun Shooter: Free Elite Shooting Games
text: Enjoyable game. Currently on Tier 14 and so far the weapons are affordable for someone who doesn't spend money on the game. On other games I happily spend £10 to £20 a month to help with progress but not on Sniper 3D. Word of advice, always read reviews, if there is an abundance of complaints about developers not responding to glitches and lost data, do not spend money on it. If you lose progress but haven't spent any money then its an inconvenience at most, you've had fun and can walk away. If you've spent money then it's a different story, don't risk it. Definitely worth a download, don't spend money and don't feel fuilty about it, plenty of ads to fund their business (I probably go through 20-30 ads a day for diamonds and extra lives).
